Practical – 11

Aim : Create an index on the course field into “students” collection. View all Indexes of a
collection “students”. Count the number of students enrolled in each distinct course. Program :
Create an index on the course field
db.students.createIndex({ course: 1 })

Output :


View all indexes of the students collection
db.students.getIndexes()

Output :


Count the number of students enrolled in each distinct course
db.students.aggregate([
{
$group: {
_id: "$course", // group by course total_students: { $sum: 1 } // count students
}
}
])






 
Output :































 
Practical – 12

Aim : Create an index on the Department field into “faculties” collection. Count the number of faculties of each distinct department.

Program :

Create an index on the department field
db.students.createIndex({ course: 1 })

Output :


Count the number of faculties in each distinct department
db.faculties.aggregate([
{
$group: {
_id: "$department", // group by department total_faculties: { $sum: 1 } // count faculties
}
}
])
Output :

